00:00:22.010 --> 00:00:25.420
PROFESSOR: OK, let's
start, so last lecture,

00:00:25.420 --> 00:00:30.790
we were talking about elasticity
as an example of a field

00:00:30.790 --> 00:00:33.600
theory-- statistical
field theory.

00:00:33.600 --> 00:00:38.110
And I ended the class by not
giving a very good answer

00:00:38.110 --> 00:00:39.690
for a question was asked.

00:00:39.690 --> 00:00:42.280
So let's go back and revisit it.

00:00:42.280 --> 00:00:44.710
So the idea that we
had was that maybe we

00:00:44.710 --> 00:00:48.560
have some kind of a lattice.

00:00:48.560 --> 00:00:55.250
And we make a
distortion through a set

00:00:55.250 --> 00:01:02.570
of vectors in however many
dimensional space we are.

00:01:02.570 --> 00:01:06.740
And in the continuum
format, we basically

00:01:06.740 --> 00:01:12.590
regarded this u as being an
average over some neighborhood.

00:01:12.590 --> 00:01:17.610
But before going to do that,
we said that the energy cost

00:01:17.610 --> 00:01:21.100
of the distortion at the
quadratic level-- of course,

00:01:21.100 --> 00:01:23.540
we can expand to go
to a higher level--

00:01:23.540 --> 00:01:28.620
was the sum over all
pairs of positions,

00:01:28.620 --> 00:01:32.180
all pairs of components,
alpha and beta data

00:01:32.180 --> 00:01:34.065
running from one to
a higher whatever

00:01:34.065 --> 00:01:39.710
the dimensionality of space
is u alpha at r or u beta

00:01:39.710 --> 00:01:40.880
at r prime.

00:01:43.460 --> 00:01:47.270
The components alphabet beta
of this vector u at these two

00:01:47.270 --> 00:01:51.690
different locations-- let's
say r and r prime here.

00:01:51.690 --> 00:01:58.720
And then there was some
kind of an object that

00:01:58.720 --> 00:02:02.800
correlated the changes here
and here maybe obtained

00:02:02.800 --> 00:02:06.070
as a second derivative
of a potential energy

00:02:06.070 --> 00:02:09.690
as a function of the
entirety of the coordinates.

00:02:09.690 --> 00:02:15.440
And this in principle
or a general function

00:02:15.440 --> 00:02:18.250
of all of these
distortions depends

00:02:18.250 --> 00:02:22.510
on all pairs of variables.

00:02:22.510 --> 00:02:28.980
But then we said that because
we are dealing with a lattice

00:02:28.980 --> 00:02:32.200
and one pair of
coordinates in the lattice

00:02:32.200 --> 00:02:34.930
is the same as another
pair of coordinates

00:02:34.930 --> 00:02:40.590
that have the same spatial
orientations that this function

00:02:40.590 --> 00:02:45.240
merely is a function
of the separation

00:02:45.240 --> 00:02:48.890
r minus r prime,
which of course can

00:02:48.890 --> 00:02:51.650
be a vector in this lattice.

00:02:51.650 --> 00:02:55.550
And the fact that
it has this form

00:02:55.550 --> 00:02:59.410
then allows us to simplify
this quadratic form

00:02:59.410 --> 00:03:04.990
rather than be a sum over
pairs and squared, if you like,

00:03:04.990 --> 00:03:09.480
into a sum over one
coordinate which

00:03:09.480 --> 00:03:14.550
is the wave vector obtained
by Fourier transform.

00:03:14.550 --> 00:03:18.810
So once we Fourier
transform, that V

00:03:18.810 --> 00:03:25.450
can be written as a sum over
just one set of K vectors,

00:03:25.450 --> 00:03:29.110
of course appropriately
discretized depending

00:03:29.110 --> 00:03:31.580
on the overall
size of the system

00:03:31.580 --> 00:03:34.950
and confined to a [INAUDIBLE]
zone that is determined

00:03:34.950 --> 00:03:40.290
by the type of wavelengths
that lattice structure allows.

00:03:40.290 --> 00:03:40.790
And

00:03:40.790 --> 00:03:43.660
Then this becomes
your alpha tilde.

00:03:43.660 --> 00:03:46.070
The Fourier
transform's evaluated

00:03:46.070 --> 00:03:51.060
at K and the other point, which
is minus K that if I write it

00:03:51.060 --> 00:03:54.730
again as K is really this.

00:03:54.730 --> 00:03:58.910
And this entity, once
we Fourier transform it,

00:03:58.910 --> 00:04:07.160
becomes a function of
the wave number K. Now,

00:04:07.160 --> 00:04:11.390
there is one statement
that is correct,

00:04:11.390 --> 00:04:16.279
which is that if I have to take
the whole lattice and move it,

00:04:16.279 --> 00:04:20.180
then essentially there
would be no cost.

00:04:20.180 --> 00:04:23.820
And moving the
entire lattice only

00:04:23.820 --> 00:04:26.840
changes the Fourier component
that corresponds to K

00:04:26.840 --> 00:04:29.890
equals to 0-- translation
of everything.

00:04:29.890 --> 00:04:39.105
So you know for sure that this
K alpha beta at K equals to 0

00:04:39.105 --> 00:04:40.325
has to be 0.

00:04:44.540 --> 00:04:47.840
Now, we did a little bit
more than that, then.

00:04:47.840 --> 00:04:55.120
We said, let's look not only at
K equals to 0, but for small k.

00:04:55.120 --> 00:04:57.850
And then for small
k, we are allowed

00:04:57.850 --> 00:05:00.800
to make an expansion of this.

00:05:00.800 --> 00:05:02.790
And this is the
expansion K squared,

00:05:02.790 --> 00:05:05.020
K to the fourth,
et cetera, that we

00:05:05.020 --> 00:05:10.570
hope to terminate at
low values of K. Now,

00:05:10.570 --> 00:05:13.850
that itself is an assumption.

00:05:13.850 --> 00:05:16.830
That's part of the
locality that i

00:05:16.830 --> 00:05:22.340
stated that I can make an
expansion as a function of K.

00:05:22.340 --> 00:05:24.340
After all, let's
say K to the 1/2

00:05:24.340 --> 00:05:27.720
is a function that goes
to 0 at K equals to 0.

00:05:27.720 --> 00:05:30.140
But it is non analytic.

00:05:30.140 --> 00:05:34.075
Turns out that in order to
generate that kind of non

00:05:34.075 --> 00:05:37.070
analyticity in
this, this function

00:05:37.070 --> 00:05:39.170
in real as a function
of separation

00:05:39.170 --> 00:05:41.420
should decay very slow.

00:05:41.420 --> 00:05:44.050
Sometimes something like
a Coulomb interaction

00:05:44.050 --> 00:05:46.220
that is very long
range will give you

00:05:46.220 --> 00:05:48.360
that kind of singularity.

00:05:48.360 --> 00:05:51.220
But things that are
really just interacting

00:05:51.220 --> 00:05:55.340
within some neighborhood or
even if they are long range,

00:05:55.340 --> 00:05:58.180
if the action falls of
sufficiently rapidly--

00:05:58.180 --> 00:06:00.700
and that's one of the things
that we will discuss later

00:06:00.700 --> 00:06:03.830
on-- precisely what
kind of potential

00:06:03.830 --> 00:06:05.800
allow you to make
an expansion that

00:06:05.800 --> 00:06:09.235
is analytical in powers
of k and hence consistent

00:06:09.235 --> 00:06:12.680
with this idea of locality.

00:06:12.680 --> 00:06:15.100
Let's also ignore
cases where you

00:06:15.100 --> 00:06:18.350
don't have inversion symmetry.

00:06:18.350 --> 00:06:22.100
So we don't need to start
and worry about anything

00:06:22.100 --> 00:06:26.110
that is linear in K. So the
first thing that I can appear

00:06:26.110 --> 00:06:29.272
is quadratic in K.

00:06:29.272 --> 00:06:33.030
Now, when we have things
that are quadratic in K,

00:06:33.030 --> 00:06:35.040
I have to make an
object that has

00:06:35.040 --> 00:06:37.940
two indices-- alpha and beta.

00:06:37.940 --> 00:06:40.900
And, well, how can I do that?

00:06:40.900 --> 00:06:43.435
Well, the kinds of things
that I mentioned last time, we

00:06:43.435 --> 00:06:46.060
could a term that is K squared.

00:06:46.060 --> 00:06:49.980
And then we have a
delta alpha beta.

00:06:49.980 --> 00:06:54.350
If I insert that over
here, what do I get?

00:06:54.350 --> 00:06:59.150
I get K squared delta alpha beta
will give me U tilde squared.

00:06:59.150 --> 00:07:04.170
So that's the term that is in
an isotropic solid identified

00:07:04.170 --> 00:07:07.840
with the shear modulus.

00:07:07.840 --> 00:07:12.250
Again, if the
system is isotropic,

00:07:12.250 --> 00:07:16.960
I don't know any distance
apart from any other distance,

00:07:16.960 --> 00:07:18.790
any direction, any
other direction.

00:07:18.790 --> 00:07:23.540
I can still make another
tensor between this

00:07:23.540 --> 00:07:28.240
is alpha and beta by
multiplying k alpha and k beta.

00:07:28.240 --> 00:07:31.480
If I then multiply
this with this,

00:07:31.480 --> 00:07:35.640
I will get K.U-- the
dot product squared.

00:07:35.640 --> 00:07:39.010
So that's the other term
that in an isotropic solid

00:07:39.010 --> 00:07:43.610
was identified with
nu plus lambda over 2.

00:07:43.610 --> 00:07:49.380
Now, as long as any direction
for K in this lattice

00:07:49.380 --> 00:07:53.080
is the same, those are
really the only terms

00:07:53.080 --> 00:07:55.830
that you can write down.

00:07:55.830 --> 00:08:00.210
But suppose that your
system was unisotropic,

00:08:00.210 --> 00:08:03.290
such as for example a
rectangular lattice.

00:08:03.290 --> 00:08:07.360
Or let's imagine we put
a whole bunch of coins

00:08:07.360 --> 00:08:10.250
here to emphasize that
rather than something

00:08:10.250 --> 00:08:12.750
like a square lattice,
we have something

00:08:12.750 --> 00:08:16.112
that is very rectangular.

00:08:16.112 --> 00:08:19.900
In this case, we can see
that the x and y directions

00:08:19.900 --> 00:08:21.940
are not the same.

00:08:21.940 --> 00:08:26.760
And there is no reason why
this K squared here could not

00:08:26.760 --> 00:08:30.440
have been separately kx
squared plus some other number

00:08:30.440 --> 00:08:31.000
ky squared.

00:08:33.770 --> 00:08:37.150
And hence, the type of
elasticity that you would have

00:08:37.150 --> 00:08:41.010
would no longer depend
on just two numbers.

00:08:41.010 --> 00:08:45.470
But, say, over here with three,
in fact there would be more.

00:08:45.470 --> 00:08:50.110
And precisely how many
independent elastic constants

00:08:50.110 --> 00:08:57.110
are given depend on the point
group symmetry-- the way

00:08:57.110 --> 00:08:59.470
that your lattice is
structured over here.

00:08:59.470 --> 00:09:02.880
But that's another story that
I don't want to get into.

00:09:02.880 --> 00:09:05.520
But last time, I
was rather careless

00:09:05.520 --> 00:09:08.920
and I said that just rotational
symmetry will give you

00:09:08.920 --> 00:09:11.360
this k squared, k alpha, k beta.

00:09:11.360 --> 00:09:14.860
I have to be more
precise about that.

00:09:14.860 --> 00:09:17.790
So this is what's happened.

00:09:17.790 --> 00:09:25.290
Now, given that you have
an isotropic material,

00:09:25.290 --> 00:09:27.940
then the conclusion is
that the potential energy

00:09:27.940 --> 00:09:30.870
will have two types of terms.

00:09:30.870 --> 00:09:32.680
There is the type
of term that goes

00:09:32.680 --> 00:09:39.080
with k squared u tilde squared.

00:09:39.080 --> 00:09:40.830
And then there's a
type of term that

00:09:40.830 --> 00:09:48.600
goes with u plus lambda over 2k
tilde k times u tilde squared.

00:09:51.497 --> 00:09:53.080
Now you can see that
immediately there

00:09:53.080 --> 00:09:57.140
is a distinction between
two types of distortion.

00:09:57.140 --> 00:10:02.170
Because if I select
my wave vector K here,

00:10:02.170 --> 00:10:07.420
any distortion that
is orthogonal to that

00:10:07.420 --> 00:10:10.630
then will not get the
contribution from this.

00:10:10.630 --> 00:10:16.840
And so the cost of those so
called transverse distortions

00:10:16.840 --> 00:10:20.160
only come from u.

00:10:20.160 --> 00:10:27.600
Whereas if I make a
distortion that is along k,

00:10:27.600 --> 00:10:31.570
it will get contribution
from both of those two terms.

00:10:31.570 --> 00:10:40.430
And hence, the cost of those
longitudinal distortions

00:10:40.430 --> 00:10:43.450
would be different.

00:10:43.450 --> 00:10:48.280
So when we go back
to our story of how

00:10:48.280 --> 00:10:56.620
does the frequency depend
on a whole bunch of ks,

00:10:56.620 --> 00:10:59.400
you can see that when
we go to the small k

00:10:59.400 --> 00:11:03.130
limit in an isotropic
material, it

00:11:03.130 --> 00:11:07.420
you've established that there
will be longitudinal mode.

00:11:07.420 --> 00:11:11.240
And we'll some kind of
longitudinal sound velocity.

00:11:11.240 --> 00:11:13.790
And in three
dimensions, there will

00:11:13.790 --> 00:11:17.200
be two branches of the
transverse mode that

00:11:17.200 --> 00:11:20.170
fall on top of each-other.

00:11:20.170 --> 00:11:23.820
As I said, once you go
to further larger K,

00:11:23.820 --> 00:11:26.640
then you can include all
kinds of other things.

00:11:26.640 --> 00:11:29.680
In fact, the types of
things that you can include

00:11:29.680 --> 00:11:32.040
at fourth order,
sixth order, et cetera

00:11:32.040 --> 00:11:36.510
again are constraints
somewhat by the symmetry.

00:11:36.510 --> 00:11:38.850
But their number proliferates.

00:11:38.850 --> 00:11:42.160
And eventually you get
all kinds of things

00:11:42.160 --> 00:11:47.290
that could potentially describe
how these modes depend.

00:11:47.290 --> 00:11:51.050
And those things are
dependent on your potential

00:11:51.050 --> 00:11:54.570
I don't know too much about.

00:11:54.570 --> 00:11:59.270
And why was this relevant
to what we were discussing?

00:11:59.270 --> 00:12:05.560
We said that basically, once
you go to some temperature other

00:12:05.560 --> 00:12:10.630
than zero, you start putting
energy into the modes.

00:12:10.630 --> 00:12:14.940
And how far in frequency you
can go given your temperature,

00:12:14.940 --> 00:12:18.460
typically, the maximum frequency
at the particular temperature

00:12:18.460 --> 00:12:20.990
is of the order of kt over hr.

00:12:24.360 --> 00:12:26.950
So that if you are at
very high temperature,

00:12:26.950 --> 00:12:31.110
all of the r1 equals [INAUDIBLE]
and all of the vibrations

00:12:31.110 --> 00:12:32.680
are relevant.

00:12:32.680 --> 00:12:35.100
But if you go to
low temperatures,

00:12:35.100 --> 00:12:38.590
eventually you hit
the regime where

00:12:38.590 --> 00:12:43.840
only these long wavelength, low
frequency modes are excited.

00:12:43.840 --> 00:12:46.020
And your heat
capacity was really

00:12:46.020 --> 00:12:50.080
proportional to how
many modes are excited.

00:12:50.080 --> 00:12:52.720
And from here, you
can see since omega

00:12:52.720 --> 00:12:56.610
goes like T, either the
case, for longitudinal

00:12:56.610 --> 00:12:59.740
or the k for
transverse has to be

00:12:59.740 --> 00:13:02.750
proportional to T the maximum 1.

00:13:02.750 --> 00:13:04.940
Larger values of
k would correspond

00:13:04.940 --> 00:13:07.840
to frequencies that
are not excited.

00:13:07.840 --> 00:13:12.140
So all of the nodes
that are down here

00:13:12.140 --> 00:13:14.370
are going to be excited.

00:13:14.370 --> 00:13:16.150
How many of them are there?

00:13:16.150 --> 00:13:20.215
Up to from 0 to
this k max that is

00:13:20.215 --> 00:13:25.120
of the order of kt over h
bar and some sound velocity.

00:13:25.120 --> 00:13:27.490
So you would say that
the heat capacity which

00:13:27.490 --> 00:13:32.920
is proportional to the number of
oscillators that you can have,

00:13:32.920 --> 00:13:37.960
you kt-- kb per oscillator.

00:13:37.960 --> 00:13:41.650
The number of oscillators
was roughly volume

00:13:41.650 --> 00:13:50.770
times kt h bar v, cubed if
you are in three dimensions.

00:13:50.770 --> 00:13:53.220
You saw that it was
one in one dimension.

00:13:53.220 --> 00:13:57.010
So in general, it will
be something like d.

00:13:57.010 --> 00:14:02.270
Of course, here, I was kind
of not very precise because I

00:14:02.270 --> 00:14:05.300
really have to separate
out the contribution

00:14:05.300 --> 00:14:09.340
of longitudinal modes and
transverse modes, et cetera.

00:14:09.340 --> 00:14:13.320
So ultimately, the
amplitude that I have

00:14:13.320 --> 00:14:15.692
will depend on a
whole bunch of things.

00:14:18.350 --> 00:14:25.500
But the functional form is
this universal t to the d.

00:14:25.500 --> 00:14:30.090
So the lesson that we would like
to get from this simple, well

00:14:30.090 --> 00:14:34.870
known example is
that sometimes you

00:14:34.870 --> 00:14:39.320
get results that are
independent in form

00:14:39.320 --> 00:14:43.280
for very different materials.

00:14:43.280 --> 00:14:46.480
I will use the
term universality.

00:14:46.480 --> 00:14:49.480
And the origin of
that universality

00:14:49.480 --> 00:14:52.960
is because we are
dealing with phenomena

00:14:52.960 --> 00:14:55.450
that involve
collective behavior.

00:14:55.450 --> 00:14:59.260
As k becomes small, you're
dealing with large wavelengths

00:14:59.260 --> 00:15:02.550
encompassing the
collective motion of lots

00:15:02.550 --> 00:15:05.045
of things that are
vibrating together.

00:15:05.045 --> 00:15:08.480
And so this kind of
statistical averaging

00:15:08.480 --> 00:15:13.330
over lots of things that are
collectively working together

00:15:13.330 --> 00:15:18.600
allows a lot of the details
to in some sense be washed out

00:15:18.600 --> 00:15:21.990
and gives you a
universal form just

00:15:21.990 --> 00:15:25.110
like adding random variables
will give you a Gaussian if you

00:15:25.110 --> 00:15:27.920
add sufficient many
of them together.

00:15:27.920 --> 00:15:30.420
It's that kind of phenomenon.

00:15:30.420 --> 00:15:32.880
Typically, we will be
dealing with these kinds

00:15:32.880 --> 00:15:34.940
of relationships
between quantities

00:15:34.940 --> 00:15:36.330
that have dimensions.

00:15:36.330 --> 00:15:38.420
Heat capacity has dimensions.

00:15:38.420 --> 00:15:40.730
Temperature has dimensions.

00:15:40.730 --> 00:15:44.410
So the amplitude
will have to have

00:15:44.410 --> 00:15:47.620
things that have dimensions
that come from the material

00:15:47.620 --> 00:15:49.640
that you are dealing with.

00:15:49.640 --> 00:15:53.325
So the thing that is
universal is typically

00:15:53.325 --> 00:15:58.200
the exponents that appear
in these functional forms.

00:15:58.200 --> 00:16:01.080
So those are the kinds
of things that we

00:16:01.080 --> 00:16:03.350
would like to capture
in different contexts.

00:16:08.640 --> 00:16:10.270
Now, as I said,
this was supposed

00:16:10.270 --> 00:16:14.546
to be just an illustration
of the typical approach.

00:16:14.546 --> 00:16:16.950
The phenomenon that
we will be grappling

00:16:16.950 --> 00:16:20.405
with for a large
part of this course

00:16:20.405 --> 00:16:22.080
has to do with
face transactions.

00:16:28.240 --> 00:16:32.410
And again, this is
a manifest result

00:16:32.410 --> 00:16:37.010
of having interaction among
degrees of freedom that

00:16:37.010 --> 00:16:41.550
causes them to collectively
behave separately differently

00:16:41.550 --> 00:16:45.810
from how a single
individual would behave.

00:16:45.810 --> 00:16:52.930
And the example
that we discussed

00:16:52.930 --> 00:16:55.370
in the previous
course and is familiar

00:16:55.370 --> 00:17:06.540
is of course that of
ice, water, steam.

00:17:06.540 --> 00:17:10.660
So here, we can look
at things from two

00:17:10.660 --> 00:17:12.720
different perspectives.

00:17:12.720 --> 00:17:17.890
One perspective, let's say
we start by-- actually,

00:17:17.890 --> 00:17:23.460
let's start with the
perspective in which I show you

00:17:23.460 --> 00:17:26.500
pressure and temperature.

00:17:26.500 --> 00:17:30.330
And as a function of
pressure and temperature,

00:17:30.330 --> 00:17:33.410
low temperatures
and high pressures

00:17:33.410 --> 00:17:41.690
would respond to having
some kind of a-- actually,

