01:16:13.815 --> 01:16:18.250
alpha running from 1 to n and
alpha of x and alpha of x.

01:16:23.320 --> 01:16:28.880
Now, if the different directions
in space are the same,

01:16:28.880 --> 01:16:31.990
then I can't have a
gradient appearing by itself

01:16:31.990 --> 01:16:34.630
because it would pick
a particular direction.

01:16:34.630 --> 01:16:38.030
In the same sense
that M squared,

01:16:38.030 --> 01:16:40.745
two Ms have to be
appearing together,

01:16:40.745 --> 01:16:43.170
if the different
directions in space

01:16:43.170 --> 01:16:46.580
forward and backward are
to be treated the same,

01:16:46.580 --> 01:16:51.452
I have to have gradients
appearing together

01:16:51.452 --> 01:16:52.440
in powers of two.

01:16:52.440 --> 01:16:56.190
So there's a term that,
before doing that,

01:16:56.190 --> 01:16:59.480
let's say also sometimes
I will write something

01:16:59.480 --> 01:17:02.880
that is M to the fourth.

01:17:02.880 --> 01:17:10.280
M to the fourth is really
