01:18:01.050 --> 01:18:03.830
M alpha appears twice.

01:18:03.830 --> 01:18:07.660
And you can go and construct
higher and higher order terms

01:18:07.660 --> 01:18:12.380
and derivatives, again
ensuring that each index

01:18:12.380 --> 01:18:18.240
both on the side of the position
x and the side of the fields M

01:18:18.240 --> 01:18:21.199
is a repeated index to
respect the symmetries that

01:18:21.199 --> 01:18:21.740
are involved.

01:18:24.740 --> 01:18:34.310
So if we-- there is actually
maybe one other thing

01:18:34.310 --> 01:18:43.200
to think about, which
is that again like

01:18:43.200 --> 01:18:48.460
before, I assume that I can make
an analytical expansion in M.

01:18:48.460 --> 01:18:50.852
And who says you
are allowed to do

01:18:50.852 --> 01:18:53.480
an analytical expansion in M?

01:18:53.480 --> 01:18:56.260
Again, the key to
that is the averaging

01:18:56.260 --> 01:18:59.110
that we have to
do in the process.

01:18:59.110 --> 01:19:05.260
And I want you to think back
to the central limit theorem.

01:19:05.260 --> 01:19:09.380
Let's imagine that there
is a variable x where

01:19:09.380 --> 01:19:15.430
the probability of
selecting that variable x

01:19:15.430 --> 01:19:18.220
is actually kind of singular.

01:19:18.220 --> 01:19:21.130
Maybe it is something
like e to the minus x

01:19:21.130 --> 01:19:23.550
that is a discontinuity.

01:19:23.550 --> 01:19:28.340
Maybe it even has an integrable
divergence at some point.

01:19:28.340 --> 01:19:30.642
Maybe it has additional
delta function.

01:19:30.642 --> 01:19:35.480
All kinds of-- it's a very
complicated, singular type

01:19:35.480 --> 01:19:38.160
of a function.

01:19:38.160 --> 01:19:41.590
Now, I tell you-- add
thousands of these variables

01:19:41.590 --> 01:19:46.390
together and tell me what the
distribution of the sum is.

01:19:46.390 --> 01:19:49.550
And the distribution of the sum,
because of the central limit

01:19:49.550 --> 01:19:53.580
theorem, you know
has to look Gaussian.

01:19:53.580 --> 01:19:59.200
So then take its log, it has
a nice analytical expansion.

01:19:59.200 --> 01:20:03.660
So the point is that
again, part of the course

01:20:03.660 --> 01:20:07.920
grading that we did to get from
whatever microscopic degrees

01:20:07.920 --> 01:20:10.680
of freedom that we
have, to reaching

01:20:10.680 --> 01:20:13.350
the level of this
effective field theory,

01:20:13.350 --> 01:20:15.870
we added many
variables together.

01:20:15.870 --> 01:20:18.320
And because of the
central limit theorem,

01:20:18.320 --> 01:20:21.615
I have a lot of confidence
