01:20:25.410 --> 01:20:27.590
But I have not.

01:20:27.590 --> 01:20:31.540
So having done all
of this, you would

01:20:31.540 --> 01:20:40.550
say that in order to describe
this magnet, what we need

01:20:40.550 --> 01:20:45.150
is to evaluate the
partition function,

01:20:45.150 --> 01:20:50.970
let's say, as a
function of temperature,

01:20:50.970 --> 01:20:55.430
which if I had
enormous power, I would

01:20:55.430 --> 01:21:01.190
do by trace of into
the beta H microscopic.

01:21:01.190 --> 01:21:04.950
But what I have done
is I have subdivided

01:21:04.950 --> 01:21:09.690
different configurations of
microscopic degrees of freedom

01:21:09.690 --> 01:21:13.590
to different configurations of
this effective magnetization.

01:21:13.590 --> 01:21:19.965
And so essentially, that sum
is the same as integrating over

01:21:19.965 --> 01:21:23.231
all configurations of this
constrained magnetization

01:21:23.231 --> 01:21:23.730
field.

01:21:26.720 --> 01:21:30.810
And the probabilities
of these configurations

01:21:30.810 --> 01:21:35.400
of the magnetization field are
exponential of this minus data

01:21:35.400 --> 01:21:39.290
H that I'm constructing
on the basis of principles

01:21:39.290 --> 01:21:43.180
that I told you-- principles
where that I first of all

01:21:43.180 --> 01:21:45.270
have a locality.

01:21:45.270 --> 01:21:49.330
I have an integrality of x.

01:21:49.330 --> 01:21:51.320
And then I have to
write terms that

01:21:51.320 --> 01:21:54.270
are consistent
with the symmetry.

01:21:54.270 --> 01:21:57.140
First term that we saw that is
consistent with the symmetry

01:21:57.140 --> 01:22:00.050
is this M squared.

01:22:00.050 --> 01:22:02.290
And let's give a name
to its coefficient.

01:22:02.290 --> 01:22:06.490
Just like the coefficient of
